http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Curb-corruption-people-told/article14021946.ece

N. Sharanappa, Principal District and Sessions Judge, has said that it was the duty of everyone to understand the Constitution and protect the rights given enunciated in it. He was addressing a gathering after unfurling the National Flag at the District Court Complex here on Tuesday.Underlining the importance of making India corruption-free to build a strong nation, Mr. Sharanappa appealed to the general public to curb corruption by taking the help of anti-corruption laws.Mr. Sharanappa also reiterated that the officials of government departments should implement programmes introduced by the governments for the welfare of the people effectively.